Hello, my name is Mohammed. I own this small LLC as my full-time (24/7) job so I'm always here and dedicated to help you at anytime if needed. I've always  enjoyed 💕 working with anything car related so this is where is see myself more handy 🔧 . 
We are here to make your car rental experience at its best. No more endless paperwork or waiting in lines forever. We've got you covered and ready to go in 5 minutes ✈️🚀🚗😌. 

                 First we have a couple of general rules 🚧 🛑 ✋🚦: 

1. If you are not happy with the car please call us immediately ☎️

2. Please bring a valid U.S driver's license. if not available, please provide us with an international driver’s license and a passport 📝 at pickup time so we will take a copy of it and verify your identity. 

3. We can either hand you the key 🔑 in person 🤼‍♀️ or send you a video 🎥 walking you through the process of where to find the keys, lockbox location and passcode. Also we will walk you through where to find the car if it was parked at the airport ✈️ parking garage or at the office location if we’re not available in person , and we have GPS tracking devices on all our cars 

4. if we’re not available in person at the airport 🛫 , the car 🚗 will be located at the 24th street parking station for both pickups and drop offs. 

5.  Please make sure to return the car 🚙  in the same pickup condition (clean🧽  and  gas⛽️  wise etc..) to avoid any additional charges/fees 💰 

6. Please make sure to be back on time ⏰ to avoid any late fees 💰💵 .You can always extend the trip time if needed if there's no other reservations on the car.

7.  We kindly ask for you to use the car locally here in Arizona 🌵  and not on a long road trip.

8. A quick reminder, you can pick-up the car anytime AFTER the trip starts (booked pick up time)and drop it off at anytime BEFORE the trip ends (booked drop off time). Late drop-offs = late fees 💵. 

9. Make sure you go through the check-in process (pick-up/drop-off) on the Turo app which includes pictures on the exterior/ interior of the car, a clear picture of the dashboard showing the gas ⛽️ level and miles . 

10. PLEASE 🙏 🙏 🙏 keep in mind that ALL money transactions/fees and other money related problems are handled by Turo and not us. We can not see 👀 any of your payment info or have the ability to charge you directly. We do not know how much you paid nor can control it. We get our pay at the END (after check-out) of the trip so we won't be able to answer or solve any or your charge 💰 concerns. So please skip us and call Turo directly with these concerns. 


For any questions ❓ concerns, please reach out to us ASAP 🏃‍♀️ 📞  through the Turo app or my personal phone number which is provided on the app and we will be happy to assist you.

Welcome to 247AUTORENT! We are a trusted host on Turo.
-Call  for booking support and question please call 702-703-4599

Below are some of the instructions and pieces of information you need to know about us and our rental.

1.) ID verification: Two photos will be requested: your valid driver's license photo and your selfie photo holding your driver's license. If you don't have it, it's expired, or you don’t feel comfortable providing it, you are unable to book.

2.) We are open 24/7; we have your time covered for morning or night pick-up and drop-off.

3.) We have a delivery service to your location or airport, but take note that this service is not free. Just choose delivery and input the location where you want us to drop off the car.

4.) Got a flat tire and a dead battery during the trip? No worries. Call Turo roadside assistance at +1 415 965 4525.

5.) Need extras? We offer baby and booster seats, prepaid fuel, one-way trips (SAN-AZ-LAS), camping tents, etc.

6.) NO PETS, NO SMOKING, OR VAPING: No smoking or pets are allowed in the vehicles. (Other renters might be allergic.) Absolutely no tobacco, marijuana, liquid, etc. smoking or vaping in the vehicle. Violators will be pursued for up to the full extent of Turo's $250 smoking fine. We are forced to utilize professional ozone decontamination when this occurs.

7.) GAS MUST BE REFILLED: Gas must be refilled back to the same level that you picked up. If you are in a hurry, do not refill the gas. We will charge a pro-rated amount of gas plus a $10 convenience fee. No hard feelings whatsoever. So the gas might not be full when you pick it up because the previous guest didn't fill it up. Just return it to the same level.

8.) Any TOLL ROAD citation or PARKING citation will be requested. Please pay the TOLL or any parking ticket if you received any! Otherwise, it will be your responsibility to pay any kind of extra fee.

We always do our best to give you a great experience with us; if you feel it, please leave a 5-star review. If the rent experience was less than satisfactory, please let us know as soon as possible so we have the opportunity to make it right.
